snippet.title: Ocean Science in the Classroom Session 8 -  Hydrothermal Vents - Amber Cobley
snippet.description:
This is session 8 of Bring Ocean Science to the Classroom! A fun, interactive session for primary ages kids to learn about the oceans and the people who work on it!

This week, I am giving our guest speakers a break and presenting myself again! 1330BST Friday 22nd May, aimed for primary but all welcome.

The first session I shared with you was about the deep sea, NOW, I am going to talk to you about one of my favourite parts of the deep sea I work on - hydrothermal vents. They are giant chimneys kilometres below the ocean surface that spew out water that is even hotter than boiling!

Surprisingly, there are many amazing animals that live at these chimneys, that can survive without sunlight! I will tell you the cool story of how...

If you want to join us live next time, here is the link to our Facebook event:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/650534399066969/
